Interface BagInterface<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
LinkedBag, ResizeableArrayBag
public interface BagInterface<T>

  • Method Summary

    Adds a new entry to this bag.

  • Method Details

    • checkIntegrity

      void checkIntegrity()
      Checks if the Bag is not corrupt
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalStateException - throws exception if the integrity is not there

    • getCurrentSize

      int getCurrentSize()
      Gets the current number of entries in this bag.
      Returns:
      The integer number of entries currently in the bag.

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Sees whether this bag is empty.
      Returns:
      True if the bag is empty, or false if not

    • add

      boolean add​(T newEntry)
      Adds a new entry to this bag.
      Parameters:
      newEntry - The object to be added as a new entry.
      Returns:
      True if the addition is successful, or false if not.

    • remove

      T remove()
      Removes one unspecified entry from this bag, if possible.
      Returns:
      Either the removed entry, if the removal was successful, or null.

    • remove

      boolean remove​(T anEntry)
      Removes one occurrence of a given entry from this bag, if possible.
      Parameters:
      anEntry - The entry to be removed.
      Returns:
      True if the removal was successful, or false if not.

    • clear

      void clear()
      Removes all entries from this bag.

    • getFrequencyOf

      int getFrequencyOf​(T anEntry)
      Counts the number of times a given entry appears in this bag.
      Parameters:
      anEntry - The entry to be counted.
      Returns:
      The number of times anEntry appears in the bag.

    • contains

      boolean contains​(T anEntry)
      Tests whether this bag contains a given entry.
      Parameters:
      anEntry - The entry to find.
      Returns:
      True if the bag contains anEntry, or false if not.

    • toArray

      T[] toArray()
      Retrieves all entries that are in this bag.
      Returns:
      A newly allocated array of all the entries in the bag. Note: If the bag is empty, the returned array is empty.

    • bagContent

      T bagContent​(int index)
      Retrieves a specific entry in the bag.
      Parameters:
      index - The location of the object in the bag.
      Returns:
      The content of a bag at a specific point "index".

    • union

      BagInterface<T> union​(BagInterface<T> bag2)
      Retrieves all entries that are in two bags.
      Parameters:
      bag2 - The second bag included in the union.
      Returns:
      An array of all of the entries in both bags.

    • intersection

      BagInterface<T> intersection​(BagInterface<T> bag2)
      Retrieves the intersection (the entries that appear in both bags) of the two bags stated. Note: If an item occurs more than once in both bags the number of items that is shared by both will be included.
      Parameters:
      bag2 - The second bag included in the intersection.
      Returns:
      An array of every entry that is shared by both bags.

    • difference

      BagInterface<T> difference​(BagInterface<T> bag2)
      Retrieves the difference of bag two (within the parameter) from bag one.
      Parameters:
      bag2 - The bag of items being taken away from bag one.
      Returns:
      An array of every entry in the first bag minus every entry that also appears in bag two.
